-I'm going.

677
01:07:02,400 --> 01:07:04,800
Just this once.
-It'll soon be over.

678
01:07:07,000 --> 01:07:08,900
Better?

679
01:07:12,900 --> 01:07:17,700
We sat on your pier. He was never
happier than at the lake.

714
01:07:18,002 --> 01:07:21,871
So I thought maybe could we borrow your cottage?
-Sure anytime. I'll get the keys.

680
01:07:25,800 --> 01:07:28,200
What is it?
-The keys to the cottage.

681
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:33,700
What for? -I'm letting Sebastien use it.
He wants to take Remy.

682
01:07:34,400 --> 01:07:38,300
Without asking me?
-I'm truly sorry.

683
01:07:38,500 --> 01:07:41,200
I'm the one who decorated it.
-That's true.

684
01:07:41,400 --> 01:07:44,400
The hours at Ikea,
don't they count.

685
01:07:44,400 --> 01:07:49,600
Or the curtains I sewed? You lend our
house to strangers without asking!

686
01:07:49,800 --> 01:07:51,900
Remy's not a stranger.

687
01:07:52,400 --> 01:07:55,000
That's why Nicole
divorced Tom Cruise!

688
01:07:55,200 --> 01:07:58,000
He'd lend their Colorado home
to anybody.

689
01:07:58,200 --> 01:08:03,200
